title: Average weekly working hours in Sweden 2019 , by type of employment
yAxis: Average number of working hours per week
summary: This is a bar chart. It shows Average number of working hours per week for 4 number of Form of Employments.
The Average number of working hours per week is highest at Form of Employment Self-employed and lowest at Form of Employment Temporary employed.
The highest Form of Employment Self-employed has 9.9 more Average number of working hours per week than the lowest Form of Employment Temporary employed.
min_summary: This bar chart has 4 columns on the x axis representing Form of Employment, and Average number of working hours per week in each Form of Employment on the y axis.
Form of Employment Self-employed has the highest Average number of working hours per week and Temporary employed has the lowest Average number of working hours per week.
mid_summary: This is a bar chart. It shows Average number of working hours per week for 4 number of Form of Employments.
The Average number of working hours per week is highest at Form of Employment Self-employed and lowest at Form of Employment Temporary employed.
The highest Form of Employment Self-employed has 9.9 more Average number of working hours per week than the lowest Form of Employment Temporary employed.
max_summary: This bar chart has 4 columns on the x axis representing Form of Employment, and Average number of working hours per week in each Form of Employment on the y axis.
The Average number of working hours per week is highest at Form of Employment Self-employed and lowest at Form of Employment Temporary employed.
Second maximum Average number of working hours per week is found at Form of Employment Permanently employed.
There is a difference of 9.9 between the maximum Form of Employment Self-employed and minimum Form of Employment Temporary employed.

The Form of Employment Self-employed has the highest Average number of working hours per week, followed by Permanently employed, and Employed total. Down to the Form of Employment Temporary employed which is the lowest.
The lowest value 25.5 at Temporary employed is almost 1.17 times smaller than the average value 30.38.
The Average number of working hours per week is 121.5 if we add up values of all Form of Employments.
